Third-party projects referenced as inspiration (permissive licenses only):

  - hugohe3/ppt-master            (MIT) — native-editable PPTX compilation,
                                          template-following design.
  - Westlake-AGI-Lab/Auto-Slides  (MIT) — academic multi-agent slide generation.
  - microsoft/markitdown          (MIT) — document -> Markdown ingestion.

This project is a clean-room, independent implementation. It deliberately does
NOT incorporate code, file structure, or copyrighted expression from any
AGPL-licensed project (including PPTist, paper-ppt-agent, and PyMuPDF). Only
ideas/requirements — which are not copyrightable — informed the design.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key runtime dependencies (all permissive — no copyleft):

  - pydantic      (MIT)  — Slide-IR validation
  - python-pptx   (MIT)  — native .pptx rendering
  - matplotlib    (BSD)  — LaTeX formula rendering (mathtext)
  - openpyxl      (MIT)  — Excel (.xlsx) ingestion
  - pdfplumber    (MIT)  — PDF text/table ingestion (pdfminer.six; NOT PyMuPDF)
  - pypdfium2     (Apache-2.0 / BSD-3) — PDF figure rendering (PDFium = BSD; NOT PyMuPDF)
  - Pillow        (MIT-CMU) — image cropping/saving for rendered figures
  - docling       (MIT, OPTIONAL extra) — Tier-2 PDF parsing backend (NOT bundled by default)

Optional Node sidecar (packages/core/formula/node — installed via `npm install`, NOT bundled;
called as an arms-length subprocess, never linked into the Python code):
  - mathjax-full       (Apache-2.0) — LaTeX → SVG (incl. mhchem chemistry, matrices)
  - @resvg/resvg-js    (MPL-2.0)    — SVG → PNG rasterization
  - langgraph     (Apache-2.0) — agent orchestration (interrupt / checkpoint / streaming)
  - fastapi       (MIT)  — HTTP API (SSE streaming + Hard-Stop resume)
  - uvicorn       (BSD)  — ASGI server (python -m asa_api)
  - python-dotenv (BSD)  — load local .env for provider keys
  - python-multipart (Apache-2.0) — multipart file uploads (web UI)

Optional provider SDKs (install only the one you use):
  - openai        (Apache-2.0) — OpenAI-compatible adapter (OpenAI/DeepSeek/aggregators/local)
  - anthropic     (MIT)  — Anthropic (Claude) adapter

## Vendored: asa-svg2pptx (packages/vendor/svg2pptx)
SVG->DrawingML compiler + SVG finalize passes, vendored from CRui5in/paper-ppt-agent at commit
6f679fc2ad410597e2e582ceab2a21c72f6bf773 (MIT License, Copyright (c) 2026 CRui5in — the last
MIT-licensed revision; the upstream project later relicensed to AGPL-3.0 and no AGPL-era code is
included). Local modifications are listed in packages/vendor/svg2pptx/README.md.
Optional raster-fallback deps (lazily imported, not required for the vector path):
svglib (LGPL-3.0 — used unmodified as a library, isolated behind an optional import) and
reportlab (BSD).
